slop-cop (Go port)
==================

This project is a Go port of the detection core of:

    awnist/slop-cop
    https://github.com/awnist/slop-cop
    AI text slop detection, 100% in browser

The Go source code, build system, CLI interface, tests, and documentation in
this repository are original works released under the MIT License (see
LICENSE).

Upstream attribution
--------------------

The pattern taxonomy, rule catalogue (rule IDs, names, descriptions, tips,
colours, LLM prompts and directives, detection hints), detector algorithms,
and word lists in the following files are derived from awnist/slop-cop:

    internal/rules/rules.go            (src/rules.ts)
    internal/detectors/word_patterns.go (src/detectors/wordPatterns.ts)
    internal/detectors/detectors.go    (src/detectors/index.ts)
    internal/detectors/helpers.go      (src/detectors/wordPatterns.ts)
    internal/llm/prompts.go            (src/detectors/llmDetectors.ts)
    internal/llm/detectors.go          (src/detectors/llmDetectors.ts)
    internal/llm/rewrite.go            (src/detectors/llmDetectors.ts)
    internal/detectors/word_patterns_test.go (src/detectors/__tests__/wordPatterns.test.ts)

At the time this port was made (April 2026), the awnist/slop-cop repository
did not carry an explicit open-source licence. Its package.json declared
`"private": true` and the GitHub repository metadata reported
`"license": null`. Publishing code on GitHub does not, by itself, grant
redistribution rights beyond those in GitHub's Terms of Service (viewing and
forking on GitHub).

If you intend to use this port in a context beyond personal use, testing, or
contribution back to the upstream author, please contact the upstream author
(@awnist) to clarify licensing for the derived taxonomy and content.

